cff-version: 1.2.0
title: >-
  ORACLE — On-chain Reputation & Audit for Coordinated
  LLM-Agent Execution
message: >-
  If you use this software, please cite it using the
  metadata from this file.
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Qiyue
    family-names: Qiu
    email: qiyueqiu777@qq.com
repository-code: 'https://github.com/qiyueqiu/ORACLE'
abstract: >-
  ORACLE binds LLM-driven agent dispatch to an on-chain
  trust and audit layer. A router agent's decision and a
  worker agent's result are co-signed into a single
  dual-role EIP-712 audit record, reconstructed and
  verified on-chain, so a dispatch is non-repudiable. The
  relay that submits transactions holds no signing key and
  cannot forge or replay an attribution. Disputes drive a
  stake-slashing loop into reputation, guarded by a circuit
  breaker that never slashes a successful execution. Three
  Solidity contracts (AgentDID, AuditLog, Reputation)
  provide the substrate, a TypeScript backend hosts the
  agents, and a React frontend drives the flow.
keywords:
  - blockchain
  - LLM agents
  - EIP-712
  - reputation
  - audit
  - agent routing
  - non-repudiation
license: MIT
version: 1.0.0
